<subSubSection id="1456F29E619AF4A73DF435179C535056" lastPageId="67" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4D15AD3E08B7314D0670D196D2F8C2E2" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E004A28D8481F15D741BDE4519F09BE" lastPageId="66" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
The type of 
<taxonomicName id="E8EFEE5ACAFCCBE16900FC9CAE8A9D88" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">
<pageBreakToken id="1E3833CE8483BDE4F8261431EE59D19C" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" start="start">Elampus</pageBreakToken>
spina
</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier) could be housed at MNHN or in the Spinola collection. A specimen of this species at MNHN is labelled: E. Panzeri F. &lt;handwritten by Lepeletier&gt; / 
<taxonomicName id="E86FF6796125C2B6AF38C06809EEE829" authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Hedychrum spina</taxonomicName>
Lep. type? &lt;handwritten by du Buysson&gt; / Museum Paris Meudon (S. et. O.) Coll. Le Peletier 160-45 &lt;partially printed, locality handwritten by du Buysson&gt;. This specimen was not considered as a type by 
<bibRefCitation id="CD7E5473899AFD51CDEBFB66C2630DF8" author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="518 - 580" title="Etude des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="66" year="1898">du Buysson (1898</bibRefCitation>
: 563; 
<bibRefCitation id="34CEB11E6D53BCA5E484E1F47D72BEF9" author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="159 - 169" title="Catalogue des Insectes Hymenopteres de la famille des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="5" year="1899">1899</bibRefCitation>
: 160), because when arrived at MNHN it was labelled only as 
<taxonomicName id="7BE2D31A76F74DA8FB1E552E954148F4" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus panzeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzeri">Elampus panzeri</taxonomicName>
by Lepeletier, without locality or identification label. It perfectly matches the original description by Lepeletier and the colour drawing furnished by the author. We would nowadays identify this specimen as 
<taxonomicName id="FEC33300540B85E3096163FD5B4F7408" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus constrictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">Elampus constrictus</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="4AA9937CCAF26F477C614F4581DE3B6B" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="0711C8162AC26EA41DD865EED31D21EE" author="Moczar, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="439 - 447" title="Ueber die Notozus-Arten Ungarns (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volume="56" year="1964 a">
<normalizedToken id="5A079FCF6913F9182A55F826CCF7F208" originalValue="Móczár">Moczar</normalizedToken>
1964a
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen in the Spinola collection could alternatively represent the type, but even in this case, there is no certainty. It perfectly matches 
<normalizedToken id="208B991690FA56AEECDE0391696A5D1D" originalValue="Lepeletier’s">Lepeletier's</normalizedToken>
description and it belongs to the species 
<taxonomicName id="CFBC1C805EB9FFA09EA9A8D6D4CC98C8" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus constrictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">Elampus constrictus</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="DA472FE425EB5ACA56FB312034745C1C" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) also.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3CD87836F9AB31FBF06FA01966E1A45B" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<normalizedToken id="641ABD4ED7FF6217B059CC3F09567B82" originalValue="Lepeletier’s">Lepeletier's</normalizedToken>
description is clear: &quot;
<normalizedToken id="10BA201E9BA46457A195141F09B5336D" originalValue="Tête">Tete</normalizedToken>
et corcelet 
<normalizedToken id="19797ED04413E39BBEBCCF07F36532C5" originalValue="d’un">d'un</normalizedToken>
vert 
<normalizedToken id="FFB5CB67E5BB669AE4F485EEC8B203F4" originalValue="bleuâtre">bleuatre</normalizedToken>
; yeux et antennes noirs. Corcelet 
<normalizedToken id="74002618E59D6B15A06025725013983C" originalValue="très-prolongé">tres-prolonge</normalizedToken>
sous 
<normalizedToken id="98017BC4DA9BFD510F39011A30548695" originalValue="l’écusson">l'ecusson</normalizedToken>
. Abdomen 
<normalizedToken id="AFFFFD4DA5C261A3F71375F3AE3A0B26" originalValue="doré">dore</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="992A4CB566807D150161A98150951455" originalValue="troisième">troisieme</normalizedToken>
segment 
<normalizedToken id="998E7D1C2FD2EA1A542221FEEFC3EA61" originalValue="échancré">echancre</normalizedToken>
. Pieds 
<normalizedToken id="5EC44289A365E658FBCD34F4F5B23E99" originalValue="d’un">d'un</normalizedToken>
vert 
<normalizedToken id="4051EE8ED7AD8685DB668926D34AAF25" originalValue="bleuâtre">bleuatre</normalizedToken>
; tarses 
<normalizedToken id="1ABA16BB2DECDD5B17CE28CEF0530C5C" originalValue="pâle">pale</normalizedToken>
. Ailes 
<normalizedToken id="584B01E7FD31029C3349E1339ACAECBE" originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
peine 
<normalizedToken id="FC94394C3749272D4E2DEC8CBAB15C6B" originalValue="enfumée">enfumee</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="C79CDA7C6CA3234041D523404F49B547" originalValue="Mâle">Male</normalizedToken>
. De Meudon&quot;. The description is completed by a colour drawing (pl. 6: 2) which shows a specimen with light green head and mesosoma, golden metasoma and small dimensions, being smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="331D84E7B8F77F4B36D8859F5F880553" authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum nitidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidum">Hedychrum nitidum</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="82E6733BB155C75F63F12CF46692BAD5" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga fervida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervida">Holopyga fervida</taxonomicName>
] and 
<taxonomicName id="2491B44FFAF5A2233F7A9405A06A4F5D" authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum lucidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidum">Hedychrum lucidum</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="E4A7D6DF25AAC8DB6F904E7AECAC290B" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga lucida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">Holopyga lucida</taxonomicName>
], and approximately as long as 
<taxonomicName id="3D65E4615FD31808BC274D754E772692" authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium roseum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseum">Hedychridium roseum</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="88F0FFB651DBB57579C63C803B5E6973" authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium roseum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseum">Hedychridium roseum</taxonomicName>
]. Description, colouration, and dimensions are different from the species considered 
<taxonomicName id="DF1B2B874A8FA545FE60C8AE01B1F99E" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="85C6F75D134D7CECE74070E97D12D18E" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="75A805E11DBD4A5CF79F460843F00167" author="Moczar, L" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="433 - 450" title="Ergebnisse der Revision der Goldwespenfauna des Karpatenbeckens (Hymenoptera: Chrysididae)." volume="10" year="1964 b">
<normalizedToken id="C5C2871ED42B2B9D8AB7316DFAC7EC9D" originalValue="Móczár">Moczar</normalizedToken>
(1964b)
</bibRefCitation>
. This species is one of the largest 
<taxonomicName id="257BAB241906F6A7AAF7F81F64C90D23" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elampus</taxonomicName>
species (up to 9 mm) in Europe, with head and mesosoma dark blue to violet and with a flame red metasoma, sometimens dark red to red-violet on the lateral sides. Even the type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="BFFA29815784365F739A93A2319322CA" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
seems to be out from the current distributional limits of 
<taxonomicName id="B9BAFE53C39FEAFB57A109B86AD5C852" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
sensu auctorum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED3894166912E42FE4837AFC7639D0F4" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
The misinterpretation of the species that the name 
<taxonomicName id="62FFA24234ABE2D31F61416195214C97" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
refers to started with 
<bibRefCitation id="0E3A616D5520BDFADD91420A42304E79" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Berlingianis, Lund" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales - Part II - Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano." year="1845">Dahlbom (1845</bibRefCitation>
: 41): Spinola sent a specimen to Dahlbom identified as 
<taxonomicName id="B3F0DDF53984747F8794E633F81488D0" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
(or 
<taxonomicName id="845EFCCFDA3F2E19A69C11E8E05F8313" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus panzeri var. spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="panzeri" variety="spina">Elampus panzeri var. spina</taxonomicName>
), which he had received from Latreille, and that clearly differs from the specimen now placed in the Spinola collection under the name 
<taxonomicName id="03C64BECEAADCB9CE67E0E210C75E4B5" lsidName="spina" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="spina">spina</taxonomicName>
Lep. coll. Latreille.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD68A05FAD88F2337DF1BE4DF9C13C86" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation id="F19911289A81F3472E6911C82C1DE706" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 42) did not describe 
<taxonomicName id="FAAD2FB93412C16BCB79E04C4099A16B" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier, but instead he described a new species received by Spinola and named 
<taxonomicName id="B057EBDBA9ED2E25A512A169B151F2F3" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Spinola: &quot;Habitat in Gallia, a D. Latreille detectus, e cujus Collectione Illustr. Spinola accepit individuum quod describendi caussa mihi benevole misit&quot;. Dahlbom's description matches the description of 
<taxonomicName id="FE77BD4D00984FF408B26B61ECEF3F7D" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus bidens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">Elampus bidens</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="E1570F8F3C189AF136BC8DD2217DE364" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853): &quot;Submagnus 2 1/4 lin. decimal. long. violascenti et purpurascenti-aeneus abdomine cyaneo-viridi, segmento 3:tio ante emarginatnram utrinque bisinuato postscutello mucronato&quot;.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ACE8FD8BE9AAC700945CEDB318069005" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation id="75FE5CD5A812310E7C21B2915BE47405" author="Abeille de Perrin, E" journalOrPublisher="Marseille" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" title="Diagnoses de Chrysides nouvelles." year="1878">Abeille (1878</bibRefCitation>
: 1, 2) replaced the name 
<taxonomicName id="0EFFECBD11E011816FDA6782367E1FCF" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom with 
<taxonomicName id="E55A4F53C068026A393AB65039DCD32B" lsidName="superbus" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="superbus">superbus</taxonomicName>
(&quot;nomen 
<normalizedToken id="4AE8354908A9FC3C4CC42F0361758610" originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
changer&quot;). Both 
<taxonomicName id="7A956AD5644573BFADA7A23D8992719D" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom and 
<taxonomicName id="19A3BF43E93C64B67A6278A58BDF4B13" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus superbus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbus">Elampus superbus</taxonomicName>
Abeille are synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="E49AD723671F816836BE7A89F6D1B0B3" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus bidens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">Elampus bidens</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1AA7A366C1A2BE2932EBA5E37E33EFA4" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Based on the type material examined in MNHN, HNHM, and LZM, the original description and drawing, 
<taxonomicName id="87DD06275D98B9D5B653B703298EEFD4" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier) (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="42427942A7A75D8CC73B599888BB0BC6" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier 1959</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="1C3312030F9C3697A0654E8EBD4B6990" author="Moczar, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="439 - 447" title="Ueber die Notozus-Arten Ungarns (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volume="56" year="1964 a">
<normalizedToken id="CD422229A5E0C34D62623BF3677EC8FA" originalValue="Móczár">Moczar</normalizedToken>
1964a
</bibRefCitation>
) is 
<taxonomicName id="BE8B32EC80FC294E62FFA780EBDBF9C0" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus frivaldszkyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frivaldszkyi">Elampus frivaldszkyi</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="6225717D1126605554C634D666B0CE5F" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) (= 
<taxonomicName id="2BC63EE70B33FEBD9E279E45AD491FF2" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus productus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">Elampus productus</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854); 
<taxonomicName id="BEFF22280B4F88511062F4FD6A534344" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus constrictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">Elampus constrictus</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="9CA9E7F35FEF9B8959E5514EB766C2EC" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) is the junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="7AD8A6D99C81E8D0F9032C8A72F118D6" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier, 1806). We suggest the neotype designation of 
<taxonomicName id="A045A03F95716D5BFC148C5E282FE59B" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
and a revision of the European species, based on recent findings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="57A834ECE4DE13467C80976E4CC45CCB" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Moreover, we note that 
<taxonomicName id="5B2F8D82B4A55CBB55759923AF48B8FA" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus panzeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzeri">Elampus panzeri</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1804) is the valid name for 
<taxonomicName id="55600848B6AF369081B219841502796B" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus scutellaris" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">Elampus scutellaris</taxonomicName>
(Panzer, 1798). A future revision of the European species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E2F993F5F1B49C4FDC0654840C1F2128" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elampus</taxonomicName>
is already planned to put in order the complex taxonomical problems of this genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7BC2137094308F0DC56FB75DE0122B93" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Since 1845 the name 
<taxonomicName id="E0E7E448AC8CB81BBF072EC5B57031CE" lsidName="spina" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="spina">spina</taxonomicName>
has been considered as a noun and not as an adjective; in fact it was used as an invariable name in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="B5C2B8EC788481C1F571B6FE4931F1B0" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elampus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AFF2CA495CAF756A55A716ED9C317DE0" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Ellampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ellampus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ellampus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="54AFCDCD952A3A4215DB5299E43C8F30" authority="Panzer, 1804" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omalus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Omalus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E1947C3B74BAC4DEBA228997D066F97F" authority="Förster, 1853" authorityName="Förster" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notozus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Notozus</taxonomicName>
in more than fifty publications. 
<bibRefCitation id="A76BB28262366BB43E73992909B91576" author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="University Press, New York" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart (1991)</bibRefCitation>
introduced the name 
<taxonomicName id="171C0BEF936B4E688A2FDE3C9801BB50" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinus">Elampus spinus</taxonomicName>
in accordance with the genus gender, but in conflict with the historical interpretation of the name and the articles 23.5 (applications to spellings) and 33.3.1 of the ICZN (when an incorrect subsequent spelling is in prevailing usage and is attributed to the publication of the original spelling, the subsequent spelling and attribution are to be preserved and the spelling is deemed to be the correct original spelling).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CB1574DC215AF2B45E54B06B8B61A3D" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<pageBreakToken id="2CDFB2EFF096187092C4B23A1C5F656F" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" start="start">Only</pageBreakToken>
three authors followed the interpretation given to the name by Kimsey and Bohart (
<taxonomicName id="F4B0C2382531606DC8DC35157E2C89D0" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinus">Elampus spinus</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0E24CC9F0F9CE0C571ED85C52AE47658" author="Tyrner, P" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, supplement" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="41 - 63" title="Chrysidoidea: Chrysididae (zlatenkoviti)." volume="11" year="2007">Tyrner 2007</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="BE1EF5ABA65E993D0C42B74A400D5B52" authority="Panzer, 1804" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omalus (Elampus) spinus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinus" subGenus="Elampus">Omalus (Elampus) spinus</taxonomicName>
(Arens 2014, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC8CCA621B73BC1D32533D406A83A485" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Linsenmaier 1999</bibRefCitation>
)) while in other publications the name 
<taxonomicName id="B171909068C1F927AB2251D8EC82E625" authority="Spinola, 1806" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Elampus spina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">Elampus spina</taxonomicName>
remained in use (Liubomirov 2007, 
<bibRefCitation id="117E72F610DE15A0A04FD85163267C0E" author="Mingo, E" journalOrPublisher="Museo Nacional de Cencias Naturales Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas, Madrid" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" title="HymenopteraChrysididae. Fauna Iberica." year="1994">Mingo 1994</bibRefCitation>
, Rosa 2005a, 2005b, 
<bibRefCitation id="2E2DC5BA47FBC952F754D2201971756D" author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="- Pierre, Aosta" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" title="I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta. Monografie del Museo regionale di Scienze naturali, St." year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E339C021B0DFD2F227115E7762B1553D" author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="Doria &quot;" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="209 - 272" title="Catalogo dei Tipi dei Crisidi del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; di Genova (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G." volume="100" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7730777AABCA87325B8D8608DF693494" author="Strumia, F" editor="Minelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Calderini (Bologna)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 10" title="HymenopteraChrysididae." volume="99" volumeTitle="Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana." year="1995">Strumia 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 2005, Strumia and Yildirim 2007, 2012, Strumia, Gayubo, Gonzalez 2010, Tussac and Zumeta 2004, Vinokurov 2008).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
